quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  16,80,"And Allah has made for you of your houses a place for comfort, and made for you houses from the hides of cattle which you find light the day you travel and the day you camp, and out of their wool and their fur and their hair (He created) household goods and things of enjoyment for a time."
  16,81,"And Allah has made for you shades from what He has created, and made for you shelters in the mountains and made for you shirts which protect you from heat and shirts which protect you in your battles."
  16,82,"This is how He perfects His favour upon you, so that you may submit. If they still turn away, then, your responsibility is only to convey the message clearly."
  16,83,"They are aware of Allah's favour, yet they deny it. And most of them are ungrateful."
  16,84,"And (remember) the Day We shall raise up a witness from every people, then the disbelievers will not be al-lowed (to make excuses) nor shall they be asked to re-pent."
  16,85,"And when the unjust will see the punishment, it will not be lightened for them, nor will they be given respite."
  16,86,"And when the Mushriks will see those whom they made partners with Allah, they will say: Our Lord, these are the partners we made whom we called in worship besides you. Then, they (the partners) will turn to them saying: You are indeed liars."
  16,87,"And on that day they will tender submission to Allah and lost to them shall be all that they used to fabricate."